        stmtIns.setString(2,rs.getString(2))
        stmtIns.setTimestamp(3,rs.getTimestamp(3))
        stmtIns.addBatch();
        i += 1
         
        if (i == batchSize) {
            def insRec = stmtIns.executeBatch();
            i = 0
            }
         
      }
     rs.close()
     stmt.close()
    
    // process the last batch
    def insRec = stmtIns.executeBatch();
    
    stmtIns.close()
    con2.commit()

You are reading in a loop the *cursor* date, copy each column value in the `insert` statement (with getXXX and setXXX) and add it to the batch (`addBatch`).

When the batch size is reached you call `executeBatch`  - this will perform *one* roundtrip to the Db and inster teh whole batch of records.

At the end of the loop you must process the last remaing rows (e.g. with batch size = 10 and 104 rows the last 4 rows).

**Dynamics**

